# SQL Order Data Analysis Project

## Overview
This project simulates a business order management system using a relational database.  
The goal is to analyze customer behavior, employee performance, and operational efficiency using SQL.

## Database Structure
The database includes the following entities:
- Customers
- Orders
- Order lines
- Employees
- Products (paper types)

Relationships are defined using primary and foreign keys.

## Key Analyses
The project focuses on answering business-related questions:

- Identifying top customers by total order amount  
- Analyzing employee workload distribution  
- Detecting delayed shipments  
- Evaluating product demand and revenue contribution  

## Techniques Used
- SQL JOIN (multi-table queries)
- Aggregation (SUM, COUNT)
- GROUP BY and HAVING
- Data modeling with relational schema

## Tools
- SQL (MySQL / PostgreSQL compatible)
